21/08/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivica Racan said on Wednesday (20 August) that he feels safe and fully trusts those working to guarantee his security. 
His comment was in response to a report in the daily <I>Globus</I> alleging that Croatian police had thwarted an assassination plan against Racan. 
He told reporters he knew nothing of such an attempt and saw no reason to dramatise the issue. 
(HINA, BBC - 20/08/03)
